with me -- is that it?

24:44.150 --> 24:46.717
You want to...
use me?

24:46.719 --> 24:49.320
Well, if it's not
too much trouble.

24:49.322 --> 24:51.422
I can't promise to be witty
and engaging,

24:51.424 --> 24:54.558
but I will get the next round.

24:54.560 --> 24:57.895
I don't think we should.

25:00.299 --> 25:02.199
No?

25:02.201 --> 25:02.967
No.

25:02.969 --> 25:06.237
If we are really going to throw
this guy off your trail,

25:06.239 --> 25:10.908
I think you should probably...

25:10.910 --> 25:13.177
have dinner with me.

25:15.982 --> 25:18.349
So, I get up at 4:00
every morning

25:18.351 --> 25:20.417
so I have time
to write my book.

25:20.419 --> 25:24.955
I'm almost at 500 pages,
single-spaced.

25:24.957 --> 25:25.923
What's it about?

25:25.925 --> 25:29.360
Well, I can't tell you that.
You might steal my idea.

25:29.362 --> 25:32.763
I'm not gonna sit down
and write a book.

25:34.534 --> 25:37.067
Well, it's about this guy
named Lance.

25:37.069 --> 25:38.736
Mm-hmm.
Short for "Lancelot."

25:38.738 --> 25:41.005
Lancelot? Like the --
Like Sir Lancelot.

25:41.007 --> 25:43.173
No. My Lance is 35

25:43.175 --> 25:46.110
and he still lives
above his parents' garage

25:46.112 --> 25:48.078
and he works at a White Castle.

25:48.080 --> 25:50.114
World-class loser, right?

25:50.116 --> 25:51.115
But the thing
about Lance

25:51.117 --> 25:53.617
is he has a million-dollar face.
Mm-hmm.

25:53.619 --> 25:57.555
He looks exactly
like Ryan Gosling.

25:57.557 --> 25:58.589
Like who?

25:58.591 --> 26:00.157
Ryan Gosling.

26:00.159 --> 26:03.060
He's an actor.
He's a famous actor.

26:03.062 --> 26:05.029
He's very famous.

26:05.031 --> 26:06.096
Okay.

26:06.098 --> 26:10.634
So, Lance has been mistaken
for Ryan Gosling 28 times.

26:10.636 --> 26:11.635
He counts the times?

26:11.637 --> 26:14.538
He counts -- 28 times.

26:14.540 --> 26:15.673
And for the last two years,

26:15.675 --> 26:18.409
Lance has studied
Ryan Gosling's films

26:18.411 --> 26:19.176
and interviews,

26:19.178 --> 26:23.013
the way he moves and walks
and everything he does.

26:23.015 --> 26:25.449
Uh-huh.
So, when Lance gets fired

26:25.451 --> 26:27.151
from White Castle,
he says to himself --

26:27.153 --> 26:30.521
he says,
"Lance, this is your moment.

26:30.523 --> 26:32.089
You're going after your dream."

26:32.091 --> 26:34.658
So, then it's all about
how he uses his resemblance

26:34.660 --> 26:39.129
to storm the Broadway scene
and Hollywood.

26:39.131 --> 26:40.097
And then what?

26:40.099 --> 26:42.366
Then you have
to read it to find out.

26:42.368 --> 26:44.435
Love to.

26:45.671 --> 26:49.707
But the ending's gonna be tragic
and funny at the same time.

26:49.709 --> 26:53.377
Does Lance get caught?

26:53.379 --> 26:55.846
Eventually, of course.

26:57.617 --> 27:01.151
Writing is very lonely, yes?

27:03.389 --> 27:04.588
I like being alone.

27:04.590 --> 27:06.023
You do?

27:06.025 --> 27:08.559
Well, your students
must be very impressed

27:08.561 --> 27:10.794
that you're a writer.

27:10.796 --> 27:11.629
No.

27:11.631 --> 27:16.533
They just think I'm a boring
high-school English teacher.

27:16.535 --> 27:17.267
Mmm!

27:17.269 --> 27:20.337
Yes, please.
Thank you.

27:20.339 --> 27:21.505
Tell me more about you.

27:21.507 --> 27:26.176
I have a sister.
Older? Younger?

27:26.178 --> 27:27.344
Older.

27:27.346 --> 27:30.280
When was the first time
you got drunk?

27:30.282 --> 27:32.449
I was in Italy with my sister.

27:32.451 --> 27:35.552
She got me drunk
on Jack Daniel's.

27:35.554 --> 27:37.621
You don't say.
The smell and --

27:37.623 --> 27:39.490
and the taste -- I can't.

27:39.492 --> 27:41.659
I hate it.
I hate it.

27:41.661 --> 27:45.562
But I drink everything else.

27:45.564 --> 27:47.231
Mmm.

27:47.233 --> 27:48.499
Ooh.

27:48.501 --> 27:51.669
♪ To be alone with you ♪

27:51.671 --> 27:54.338
Ooh, I finished
that one very quickly.

27:57.243 --> 27:58.709
I like to look at you.

27:58.711 --> 28:01.812
I love your accent.

28:01.814 --> 28:03.747
That went down good.

28:03.749 --> 28:05.582
Wait.
One more.

28:05.584 --> 28:09.219
Cheers.

28:09.221 --> 28:10.721
Bioinformatics

28:10.723 --> 28:16.493
and how they can apply
to cancer treatment.

28:16.495 --> 28:17.728
Bio what?

28:17.730 --> 28:18.762
Informatics.

28:18.764 --> 28:22.800
Advanced computer systems
that can read biological data.

28:22.802 --> 28:24.168
It's a --

28:24.170 --> 28:25.502
It's a think tank.

28:25.504 --> 28:28.305
What do you do for them?
Well, nothing, actually.

28:28.307 --> 28:31.241
I work for a philanthropist
in Tampa.

28:31.243 --> 28:33.210
He is considering funding them.

28:33.212 --> 28:36.113
I'm here to check out
the C.E.O.

28:36.115 --> 28:38.148
Philanthropy.

28:38.150 --> 28:39.650
Mm-hmm.

28:39.652 --> 28:41.485
Damn, Javier.

28:41.487 --> 28:44.488
You are doing good
in this world.

28:54.266 --> 28:56.600
I have another confession.

28:56.602 --> 28:58.736
Yeah?
What is that?

28:58.738 --> 29:00.971
I'm not a blonde.

29:08.180 --> 29:10.914
Are you mad?

29:10.916 --> 29:13.283
You look mad.

29:46.719 --> 29:51.221
♪♪

29:53.959 --> 29:55.893
♪ Waking down,
waking why ♪

29:55.895 --> 29:57.594
♪ Looking times,
wonder na ♪

29:57.596 --> 30:00.597
♪ Making baby, shaking lady,
girlfriend, girlfriend ♪

30:00.599 --> 30:02.800
♪ Pass the ball, we pass it
back, my friend ♪

30:02.802 --> 30:06.703
♪ Behind, rumbling, catch me
while you're smiling so warm ♪

30:06.705 --> 30:10.340
♪ Girlfriend, girlfriend,
me pumping like your fella ♪

30:10.342 --> 30:13.877
♪ Me need to play, I need to
play, I need to play, yeah ♪

30:13.879 --> 30:17.514
♪ Girlfriend, girlfriend,
we go tall as hell now ♪

30:17.516 --> 30:20.484
♪ Come a little closer
till I stop ♪

30:20.486 --> 30:22.719
♪ She got -- ♪

30:31.330 --> 30:34.798
<i>You will call her</i>
<i>at exactly 10:15 a.m.</i>

30:34.800 --> 30:38.535
<i>and tell her</i>
<i>you can't find your wallet.</i>

30:43.309 --> 30:48.545
[ Shower running ]

31:27.386 --> 31:30.420
Javier: Letty, you up?

31:31.924 --> 31:33.557
Letty?

31:33.559 --> 31:35.525
Yeah, I'm up.

31:35.527 --> 31:38.729
How you feeling?

31:38.731 --> 31:41.298
Like death.

31:41.300 --> 31:44.801
I have a meeting this morning.

31:44.803 --> 31:47.571
With the think tank?

31:47.573 --> 31:49.506
Right.

31:49.508 --> 31:51.642
On a Sunday?

31:51.644 --> 31:55.512
I wanted to have breakfast
with you.

31:55.514 --> 31:57.881
I'll have dinner.

31:57.883 --> 32:00.884
Are you staying here tonight?

32:00.886 --> 32:02.052
[ Turns off shower ]

32:02.054 --> 32:05.489
I'd stay
if you want to see me again.

32:06.058 --> 32:10.761
I'll have dinner
with you tonight, definitely.

32:15.534 --> 32:17.935
You're dressed.

32:17.937 --> 32:21.905
Almost.

32:21.907 --> 32:23.640
Thank you.

32:23.642 --> 32:25.575
I'm gonna go back
to my apartment,

32:25.577 --> 32:26.610
get a shower there.

32:26.612 --> 32:28.345
You can stay here
while I'm gone.

32:28.347 --> 32:32.482
I need to let my dog out,
get some papers graded.

32:32.484 --> 32:34.518
Okay.

32:39.358 --> 32:41.491
I'll see you tonight.

32:41.493 --> 32:43.527
Yeah.

32:45.364 --> 32:46.029
I need a car.

32:46.031 --> 32:49.700
Your car is waiting right here,
ma'am, right here, right here.

32:49.702 --> 32:51.902
Let 619 know
their car service

32:51.904 --> 32:54.571
is running about
five minutes late, okay?

32:54.573 --> 32:56.573
Five minutes.

32:59.111 --> 33:01.111
712 Hamlet Court.

33:01.113 --> 33:04.314
I'm sorry,
but I need you to speed.

33:15.127 --> 33:16.493
Stop the car.

33:16.495 --> 33:17.427
I take you all the way.

33:17.429 --> 33:20.564
I don't want you
to take me all the way.

33:40.252 --> 33:42.953
See you in a little bit, honey.

33:46.392 --> 33:48.692
All right,
let's get in the car.

33:48.694 --> 33:51.595
Let's go.

33:51.597 --> 33:55.065
[ Starts car ]

34:02.641 --> 34:06.276
[ Tinnitus ]

34:06.278 --> 34:09.913
[ Groans ]

34:15.020 --> 34:17.988
[ Groans ]

34:49.221 --> 34:51.955
[ Doorbell chimes ]

34:58.063 --> 34:59.596
Hi.

34:59.598 --> 35:01.298
You're Daphne?

35:01.300 --> 35:03.300
Yes.
Do we know each other?

35:03.302 --> 35:06.470
No, but there's a man
coming here to kill you.

35:06.472 --> 35:08.839
I'm sorry --
Look, I know this sounds crazy.

35:08.841 --> 35:11.074
A little bit.
Who are you?

35:11.076 --> 35:13.477
Doesn't matter.
His name is Javier.

35:13.479 --> 35:15.679
Your husband hired him.

35:15.681 --> 35:17.180
You should go.

35:17.182 --> 35:18.281
Chase.
What?

35:18.283 --> 35:20.517
Your husband's
name is Chase, right?

35:20.519 --> 35:22.252
Chase gave Javier
a floor plan,

35:22.254 --> 35:24.187
a key to your house,
a photo of you,

35:24.189 --> 35:26.723
and $50,000 to kill you.

35:26.725 --> 35:29.292
Look, I am trying to help you.

35:29.294 --> 35:30.393
Can you think of any reason

35:30.395 --> 35:32.028
your husband
might want you dead,

35:32.030 --> 35:34.397
or is this a total shock?

35:38.670 --> 35:40.770
In two minutes, your husband
is going to call you.

35:40.772 --> 35:42.405
He'll tell you
he can't find his wallet.

35:42.407 --> 35:45.742
He'll ask you to go upstairs
and check his bedside table.

35:45.744 --> 35:48.145
Can we take the car
in the driveway?

35:48.147 --> 35:49.179
I-I'm not leaving with you.

35:49.181 --> 35:51.281
By the time your husband calls,
it'll be too late.

35:51.283 --> 35:53.650
The point of the phone
call is to get you upstairs so

35:53.652 --> 35:56.920
that Javier can break in
and kill you.

35:59.158 --> 36:01.458
Wait. Wait. Wait. Stop.
No, but I thought --

36:01.460 --> 36:04.227
He's here.
Is there a gun in the house?

36:04.229 --> 36:06.396
Yeah.
Show me.

36:12.704 --> 36:15.739
[ Mobile phone vibrating ]

36:15.741 --> 36:17.507
Answer it.

36:17.509 --> 36:22.312
Hi, baby.
No. It's fine.

36:22.314 --> 36:24.514
Your wallet.

36:24.516 --> 36:26.550
Sure.
I can check.

36:26.552 --> 36:28.952
I-I'm up here anyway.

36:34.693 --> 36:36.293
Your wallet's not up here.

36:36.295 --> 36:40.297
Do you want me to check
downstairs or anywhere?

36:40.299 --> 36:42.399
Loaded?

36:42.401 --> 36:43.767
Okay.

36:43.769 --> 36:47.437
You and Tyler have fun.

36:47.439 --> 36:49.639
Call 911 now.

37:02.354 --> 37:03.753
Why are you running the shower?

37:03.755 --> 37:05.388
Did you call the police?

37:05.390 --> 37:06.356
Yes.
Get in the closet.

37:06.358 --> 37:08.325
Hide behind the clothes,
turn off your phone,

37:08.327 --> 37:09.693
and don't even breathe.
Are you sure --

37:09.695 --> 37:11.861
Javier's here.
The police aren't.

37:11.863 --> 37:14.497
We have to deal with this.

37:37.856 --> 37:40.624
[ Cocks gun ]

38:37.916 --> 38:42.319
You have a shotgun
pointed at your back.

38:42.321 --> 38:46.890
Don't turn around.
Don't move.

38:46.892 --> 38:49.225
Drop the gun.

38:49.227 --> 38:53.163
Don't make the mistaking
thinking I'll tell you again.

39:00.572 --> 39:01.805
Kick it away.

39:01.807 --> 39:05.008
[ Gun slides
across floor ]

39:05.010 --> 39:07.877
Now put your hands
above your head

39:07.879 --> 39:11.581
and turn around, slowly.

39:23.528 --> 39:26.863
So, you're not
an English teacher.

39:26.865 --> 39:29.699
No.

39:29.701 --> 39:31.434
You're a cop.

39:31.436 --> 39:33.470
No.

39:34.039 --> 39:38.541
I was in your room yesterday
when you and Chase came in.

39:38.543 --> 39:39.008
My room?

39:39.010 --> 39:43.880
I was in the closet,
heard everything you said.

39:45.851 --> 39:48.852
You're a thief.

39:48.854 --> 39:52.489
Well, then,
we can work this out.

39:52.491 --> 39:54.657
How's that?

39:56.461 --> 40:01.064
May I get something
out of my pocket?

40:01.066 --> 40:03.933
Slowly.

40:06.638 --> 40:09.773
The 4Runner
in the driveway is new.

40:09.775 --> 40:11.574
There is a bag with fif--

40:11.576 --> 40:12.409
$50,000 in cash

40:12.411 --> 40:15.912
and all the info
you need to kill Daphne.

40:15.914 --> 40:17.347
Take the car.

40:17.349 --> 40:19.749
Take the money.

40:19.751 --> 40:23.686
What, and you just
kill Daphne anyway?

40:23.688 --> 40:25.622
Yes.

40:25.624 --> 40:28.691
Letty, go.

40:33.999 --> 40:37.967
Ever feel like you crossed
a line you didn't see?

40:39.104 --> 40:44.007
Did my husband
pay you to kill me?

40:44.009 --> 40:45.942
Daphne.

40:45.944 --> 40:47.877
Why?

40:49.981 --> 40:53.483
I have no idea.

40:53.485 --> 40:55.785
But I am sure you do.

40:59.024 --> 41:00.123
G-Give it to me.

41:00.125 --> 41:01.991
I could kill you
right this second.

41:01.993 --> 41:05.028
Daphne, Daphne, calm down.

41:06.698 --> 41:09.365
Drop the keys on the floor.

41:13.772 --> 41:15.805
Take them.
Get out of here.

41:15.807 --> 41:18.875
What are you talking about?
The police are coming.

41:18.877 --> 41:19.909
They'll arrest you, too.

41:19.911 --> 41:21.644
Take his car and the money.

41:21.646 --> 41:23.546
I'm not leaving you alone.

41:23.548 --> 41:25.014
I'll be fine.

41:25.016 --> 41:27.750
Daphne, Daphne...

41:27.752 --> 41:30.620
You saved my life.

41:30.622 --> 41:32.655
Go!

41:44.436 --> 41:47.270
[ Car alarm chirps ]

41:57.516 --> 42:00.950
[ Sirens approaching ]

42:28.313 --> 42:32.315
♪♪

43:21.499 --> 43:24.601
Pathetic.

43:24.603 --> 43:26.936
Hi, Mom.

43:31.610 --> 43:33.710
I want to see Jacob.

43:33.712 --> 43:36.346
Yeah, that's not gonna happen.

43:38.049 --> 43:38.681
Is he inside?

43:38.683 --> 43:40.750
You're violating
your restraining order

43:40.752 --> 43:43.820
just standing there.

43:43.822 --> 43:45.254
I've got something for him.

43:45.256 --> 43:46.656
You want to
give him something?

43:46.658 --> 43:49.525
Let it be your absence
from his life.

43:49.527 --> 43:54.364
I mean, shit,
at least give the kid a chance.

43:56.301 --> 43:58.534
You're so mean.

44:00.739 --> 44:04.374
I signed him up
for baseball.

44:04.376 --> 44:08.578
Please, Mom,
I haven't seen him in two years.

44:14.519 --> 44:16.719
I'll call the cops
if that's what it takes

44:16.721 --> 44:19.656
to get you off my property.

44:19.658 --> 44:21.658
Five minutes.

44:21.660 --> 44:24.394
I'd say you've got about three.

44:38.743 --> 44:41.044
Please!

44:46.651 --> 44:49.385
[ Mouthing ]

45:21.519 --> 45:25.221
[ Mobile phone vibrating ]

45:38.203 --> 45:40.737
[ Vibrating stops ]

45:49.881 --> 45:52.949
Have you seen Crissy
around?

45:52.951 --> 45:55.752
[ Honking ]

46:04.763 --> 46:08.431
Shane from the diner
texted you about me?

46:10.568 --> 46:12.835
$200 a gram.

46:14.405 --> 46:16.038
How much you got?

46:16.040 --> 46:19.408
I don't know.
A couple ounces.

46:19.410 --> 46:21.043
$150 a gram,
and I'll take it all.

46:21.045 --> 46:26.749
Not Sam's Club.
Take it or fucking don't.

46:26.751 --> 46:28.918
Fine.

46:28.920 --> 46:30.787
You got the money?

46:30.789 --> 46:33.823
Yeah.

46:33.825 --> 46:36.225
Wait there.

46:38.696 --> 46:41.731
Hey, Christian, it's Letty.

46:41.733 --> 46:44.433
I'm sorry
I missed our appointment.

46:44.435 --> 46:48.638
I'm sorry I've been
dodging your calls.

46:48.640 --> 46:52.308
I'm sorry
I'm getting back to you so late.

46:52.310 --> 46:54.777
I'm just...

46:54.779 --> 46:57.980
I'm sorry.

46:57.982 --> 47:00.082
Things went to hell
in Asheville.

47:00.084 --> 47:05.588
So I took a little road trip
that didn't turn out so great.

47:05.590 --> 47:08.724
I'll be honest.
I've been better.

47:08.726 --> 47:11.727
Don't get mad,
but I'm about to do a swan dive

47:11.729 --> 47:14.964
off the back of a wagon,

47:14.966 --> 47:18.267
pay a little visit
to rock bottom.

47:20.371 --> 47:22.505
It's not your fault.

47:22.507 --> 47:27.276
You're not allowed
to feel guilty about this.

47:27.278 --> 47:29.445
It's me.

47:29.447 --> 47:31.714
I'm a piece of shit.

47:32.951 --> 47:37.520
Why keep fighting it, you know?

47:37.522 --> 47:39.856
So...

47:39.858 --> 47:42.358
Thanks for everything.

47:51.402 --> 47:54.003
Woman: I'm able to express
my emotions

47:54.005 --> 47:57.073
in a healthful, positive way.

47:57.075 --> 48:01.277
♪♪

48:13.491 --> 48:16.926
I am centered
and well-balanced.

48:19.264 --> 48:24.934
♪ It's a fine time
to trade animals ♪

48:24.936 --> 48:27.603
I can feel
how beautiful I am.

48:27.605 --> 48:31.941
♪ No, we'll never die
or show anyway ♪

48:31.943 --> 48:36.512
♪ The signs
of great concern ♪

48:38.016 --> 48:41.651
I am utterly,
perfectly me.

48:43.321 --> 48:47.823
♪ It's the right time
to write back home ♪

48:47.825 --> 48:51.928
♪ To share what I've learned
and earned ♪

48:51.930 --> 48:53.529
♪ You see, we're never right ♪

48:53.531 --> 48:59.702
♪ The credit compares
what we've already learned ♪

48:59.704 --> 49:04.206
♪ I keep seeing your eyes ♪

49:04.208 --> 49:08.711
♪ In slo-mo ♪

49:08.713 --> 49:12.081
♪ I keep telling the lies ♪

49:12.083 --> 49:16.385
♪ In slo-mo ♪

49:17.789 --> 49:20.456
Oh, it's so good
to see you!

49:20.458 --> 49:22.825
Now, tell everything with Nana.

49:22.827 --> 49:24.226
I'm really good at math.

49:24.228 --> 49:26.629
Yeah?
I got an A-plus-plus.

49:32.603 --> 49:34.971
Nice place you've got here.

49:38.042 --> 49:40.943
Looks like you crossed back
over that line.

49:40.945 --> 49:41.877
Please.

49:41.879 --> 49:45.014
So, how much of my money did
you destroy yourself with, huh?

49:45.016 --> 49:47.116
There's $18,000 left.

49:47.118 --> 49:48.551
Shit.

49:48.553 --> 49:51.887
Well, at least you gave
some of it to your son.

49:51.889 --> 49:52.955
How do you know?

49:52.957 --> 49:56.225
Because I know everything
about you, Leticia Ann Raines.

49:56.227 --> 50:01.864
Born October 15, 1983,
mother Estelle, father --

50:01.866 --> 50:03.532
who the hell knows?

50:03.534 --> 50:06.902
10th-grade dropout,
16-year-old runaway.

50:06.904 --> 50:08.871
1999, petty theft.

50:08.873 --> 50:12.508
2000, intoxication
in a public place.

50:12.510 --> 50:14.043
2002, larceny.

50:14.045 --> 50:18.748
2006, Jacob Michael Raines
born, father --

50:18.750 --> 50:20.649
father -- who the hell knows?

50:20.651 --> 50:25.021
2012, possession
of a controlled substance

